    "content" : "This is how you add a picture to a forum post.\n<br> \n<br> Two ways to do this:\n<br> \n<br> \n<br> \n<span class=\"glow\" style=\"display:inline;padding:0 6px;color:#fff;text-shadow:0 0 1em red,0 0 1em red,0 0 1.2em red\">1.</span>Click on the attachments option (\n<span class=\"shadow\" style=\"display:inline;padding:0 6px;color:blue;text-shadow:-2px 2px 2px #999\">underneath Save Draft, Preview, and Submit</span>) options:\n<br> \n<div class=\"inline-attachment\"> \n <dl class=\"file\"> \n  <dt class=\"attach-image\">\n   <img src=\"./download/file.php?id=11129&amp;sid=088b8853de3b7c7127199ac077478ac2\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-12-19 at 23.38.43.png\" onclick=\"viewableArea(this);\">\n  </dt> \n  <dd>\n   Screen Shot 2015-12-19 at 23.38.43.png (12.56 KiB) Viewed 34803 times\n  </dd> \n </dl> \n</div> Click the \n<span class=\"shadow\" style=\"display:inline;padding:0 6px;color:blue;text-shadow:-2px 2px 2px #999\">Add Files</span> button.\n<br> \n<br> \n<div class=\"inline-attachment\"> \n <dl class=\"file\"> \n  <dt class=\"attach-image\">\n   <img src=\"./download/file.php?id=11130&amp;sid=088b8853de3b7c7127199ac077478ac2\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-12-19 at 23.40.11.png\" onclick=\"viewableArea(this);\">\n  </dt> \n  <dd>\n   Screen Shot 2015-12-19 at 23.40.11.png (11.89 KiB) Viewed 34803 times\n  </dd> \n </dl> \n</div> \n<br> \n<br> Select one or more images (you want to add to a message). Hold down the \n<span class=\"shadow\" style=\"display:inline;padding:0 6px;color:blue;text-shadow:-2px 2px 2px #999\">shift key</span>(to select more than one image).\n<br> \n<br> Click the \n<span class=\"shadow\" style=\"display:inline;padding:0 6px;color:blue;text-shadow:-2px 2px 2px #999\">Open</span> button.\n<br> \n<br> The images will be uploaded.\n<br> \n<br> Once uploaded, (you will see them), position (your cursor) where you want to add the images, and click the \n<span class=\"shadow\" style=\"display:inline;padding:0 6px;color:blue;text-shadow:-2px 2px 2px #999\">Place inline</span> button.\n<br> \n<br> You will see an \"\" appears in your forum post (message).\n<br> \n<div class=\"inline-attachment\"> \n <dl class=\"file\"> \n  <dt class=\"attach-image\">\n   <img src=\"./download/file.php?id=11131&amp;sid=088b8853de3b7c7127199ac077478ac2\" class=\"postimage\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2015-12-19 at 23.43.33.png\" onclick=\"viewableArea(this);\">\n  </dt> \n  <dd>\n   Screen Shot 2015-12-19 at 23.43.33.png (29.59 KiB) Viewed 34803 times\n  </dd> \n </dl> \n</div> Click the \n<span class=\"dropshadow\" style=\"display:inline;padding:0 6px;color:blue;text-shadow:-1px 1px 0 #999\">Submit button</span>, to (finish) your forum post, or \n<span class=\"dropshadow\" style=\"display:inline;padding:0 6px;color:blue;text-shadow:-1px 1px 0 #999\">Preview</span>to see what it will look like.\n<br> \n<br> \n<br> \n<br> \n<br> \n<span class=\"shadow\" style=\"display:inline;padding:0 6px;color:blue;text-shadow:-2px 2px 2px #999\">2.</span> If you are using a third-party image hosting service like flikr, \n<br> \n<br> You need to link your image (in flikr) to your Post.\n<br> \n<br> Click the\n<span class=\"shadow\" style=\"display:inline;padding:0 6px;color:blue;text-shadow:-2px 2px 2px #999\">Insert Image</span>button, OR just copy these tags into your message:\n<br> \n<br> \"[img].....[/img]\"\n<br> \n<br> Put the website address of your image in between the tags.\n<br> \n<br> For example \n<a href=\"http://chocksaway.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/chocksaway_shield1.png\" class=\"postlink\">http://chocksaway.com/blog/wp-content/u ... hield1.png</a> would go in between the [img].....[/img]\n<br> \n<br> Click the \n<span class=\"glow\" style=\"display:inline;padding:0 6px;color:#fff;text-shadow:0 0 1em red,0 0 1em red,0 0 1.2em red\">Submit</span> or \n<span class=\"glow\" style=\"display:inline;padding:0 6px;color:#fff;text-shadow:0 0 1em red,0 0 1em red,0 0 1.2em red\">Preview</span>button.",
